Carlos Allende, a nephew of the late  Chilean president Salvador Allende, was found dead in his hotel room here  Monday, police said.
Allende, 52, apparently died of heart attack, sources said.
His body was found by firemen alerted by hotel personnel after Allende was  not seen for 24 hours. Heart medicine was found in his room, one staffer said.
Allende was born in Chile but had French nationality and lived in Paris.
He worked for French television as a producer and was in Cannes covering  the film festival.
Allende came to France in the early 1970s to work as an intern for French  television. When his uncle was overthrown by General Augusto Pinochet in 1973,  Allende was unable to return to Chile and remained in France.
Salvador Allende died in the coup.
